<subSubSection box="[151,730,1158,1184]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,730,1158,1184]" box="[151,730,1158,1184]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,730,1158,1184]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
2. 
<taxonomicName authority="BURMEISTER, 1838" authorityName="BURMEISTER" authorityYear="1838" box="[181,730,1158,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Meconematinae">MECONEMATINAE BURMEISTER, 1838</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,1230,1365]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
This subfamily is represented in 
<collectingCountry box="[518,586,1231,1257]" name="Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Brazil</collectingCountry>
by six genera and 18 species, 15 of them within the tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eichler" authorityYear="1938" box="[1235,1355,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Phlugidini">Phlugidini</taxonomicName>
, a tribe exclusively distributed in the tropics. They are predatory katydids presenting anterior raptorial legs (Chamorro-Rengifo &amp; Braun 2016). We collected four species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Stal, 1861" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1861" box="[782,994,1302,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Phlugis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[782,868,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Phlugis</emphasis>
Stål, 1861
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eichler" authorityYear="1938" box="[1011,1134,1303,1330]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Phlugidini">Phlugidini</taxonomicName>
), which represent the first record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="BURMEISTER" authorityYear="1838" box="[260,439,1339,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Meconematinae">Meconematinae</taxonomicName>
for the 
<collectingRegion box="[527,670,1339,1365]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Paraná State</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
